@@TJvAlarms
<TITLEIMG TJvAlarms>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.System.AlarmsAndTimers.Alarms
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Programmable timer.
Description
  TJvAlarm is a non-visible component that provides you with a programmable timer. The component allows
  multiple alarms to be added, each of which can be set to repeat at a specified interval or not at
  all.

  To add scheduled tasks to you application you should:

  * Drop a TJvAlarms on a form or data module.
  * Write a handler for the <LINK TJvAlarms.OnAlarm, OnAlarm> event.
  * Set the Active property to True.
  * Add tasks to the component using the Add method in run time or the Alarms property editor in design
    time.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAlarms.Active
Summary
  Indicates if alarms will trigger.
Description
  Active indicates if alarms will fire. When Active is set to False, no alarm will fire at the set
  date/time. When set to True, Alarms will fire at the set date/time.
See Also
  TJvAlarms.Running

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAlarms.Add
Summary
  Adds a new alarm.
Description
  Add adds a new alarm to the component. To add an alarm you need to provide a name (the alarm's ID), a
  date/time when the alarm should fire and the kind of alarm (default's to one-shot).
Parameters
  AName - Name of the alarm. The name is the only way you can identify an alarm during an OnAlarm
           event.
  ATime - Date and time at which the alarm should go off.
  AKind - The kind of alarm to be added. Kind will default to tkOneShot, meaning that the alarm will
           fire only once and at the specified time.
See Also
  TJvAlarms.Alarms, TJvAlarms.Delete, TJvAlarms.OnAlarm, TJvTriggerKind

